      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>In step 7 of fatty-acid biosynthesis (Figure 29.6), dehydration of a <i>β</i>-hydroxy thioester occurs to give <i>trans</i>-crotonyl ACP. Is the dehydration a syn elimination or an anti elimination?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdThaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0d34e0c4daadff281d330accf0a0fc4f36e1530c/OChem_29_EC_020.jpg\" alt=\"A beta hydroxy thioester is dehydrated to form trans-crotonyl A C P. The C-C single bond in the reactant converts to a double bond in the product.\">",
